Description: Syngas from gasified agricultural waste or poultry litter
Blast-furnace gas also converter gas or LDG or Finex gas (approx 10% of the heat content of pipeline gas)
Biogas from digestion of agricultural waste or food waste or other organic material
Biomass excluding wood chips but including agricultural waste and energy crops
Bioderived liquid fuels such as palm oil or vegetable oils or biodiesel or bio-oil or other bioliquids
Coal syngas - fuel for IGCC plants (from gasified coal )
Coke oven gas (approximately 50% of the heat content of pipeline natural gas)
Coal seam gas (aka coal bed gas or coal bed methane or CBM)
Flare gas or wellhead gas or associated gas
Liquified petroleum gas (usually butane or propane)
Mine gas (methane from active or abandoned coal mines)
Natural gas liquids, also natural gas condensate
Gasified crude oil or refinery bottoms or bitumen
Orimulsion, trade name for emulsified bitumen manufactured in Venezuela - production terminated in 2006
Private power company - independent power producer
Unknown operational status, typically assigned to old plant
Syngas from gasified wood or biomass
Waste gas or low calorific gas (LCV from refinery or other industrial processes)
